1
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:58,600
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, COMPANIES,

2
00:00:58,683 --> 00:01:00,935
AND INCIDENTS IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:32,675
This is all worn out,
but go ahead and use it.

4
00:01:33,384 --> 00:01:34,344
Thank you.

5
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,390
You take the umbrella.

6
00:01:39,474 --> 00:01:42,393
Ms. Han needs me, so I need to hurry back.

7
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:47,357
Wait.

8
00:01:58,034 --> 00:01:59,786
It's not good to get soaked in acid rain.

9
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:00,912
Let's go together.

10
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,990
EPISODE 6

11
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:08,688
Aren't you from our hospice?

12
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:10,773
Why are you here?

13
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:14,277
Hey!

14
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:21,159
Where are you running off to?

15
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:23,411
I'm not running off.
I'm on my way to see my mom.

16
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,163
Where is your mom?

17
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:27,498
She got married to some guy.

18
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,377
Please don't tell my brother.

19
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:33,338
Where is your mom?

20
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:37,050
My brother had hid this, but I found it.

21
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:40,970
You can't go there all by yourself.

22
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,764
Tell your mom to meet you here.

23
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:45,099
She doesn't like coming to see me.

24
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,358
Let me out!

25
00:03:53,441 --> 00:03:55,735
You said your mom
doesn't like coming to see you.

26
00:03:56,861 --> 00:03:59,864
I have to give her my gift
for her birthday.

27
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:04,953
She sent me this as a gift on my birthday,

28
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:08,456
so I want to give her a gift too!

29
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:10,458
Then go with your brother.

30
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:13,836
If he finds out, he'll be like,
"You crazy idiot."

31
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:15,755
He'll totally say that.

32
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:19,509
You can't go in your current condition.
Later on, when you're fully recovered--

33
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:21,427
I'm never going to get better.
I know that.

34
00:04:35,316 --> 00:04:38,611
I'm not going back to the hospice.
I have to go see my mom.

35
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:39,946
Let me out!

36
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:42,824
Dr. Lee, you're mean.

37
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:44,993
You're a dumb meanie.

38
00:04:58,464 --> 00:04:59,924
Gongju is about three hours away.

39
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:01,551
I'll wake you up when we get there.

40
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:08,451
Here goes.

41
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,921
Tae-hyun.

42
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:34,560
Have some food.

43
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:36,938
I don't feel like eating.

44
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:41,776
Still, you have to eat.

45
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:45,863
Being the glutton you are, you haven't
eaten anything since yesterday morning.

46
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,616
Who says gluttons can't lose appetite?

47
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,577
Just leave me alone already.

48
00:06:56,916 --> 00:07:00,211
Are you acting like this because
you feel guilty about Mr. Kim's death?

49
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,257
Why would I feel guilty?

50
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:08,010
He was terminally ill
and bound to die any day.

51
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,137
Why is that my fault?

52
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:13,015
I'm mad because my Overwatch account
is suspended for a month!

53
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:17,562
Right, it's not your fault
that he passed away.

54
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:22,150
He wanted to go to heaven
and eat better jajangmyeon.

55
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,651
That's why he passed away.

56
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:25,903
Don't beat yourself up.

57
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,160
I'll just leave the porridge here, then.

58
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:52,680
Why would I beat myself up?
I'm not an idiot like you!

59
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,439
Jajangmyeon in heaven? Give me a break.

60
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:06,319
People take advantage of you
because you still believe such bullshit.

61
00:08:06,402 --> 00:08:07,445
You moron.

62
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:16,120
I bet that idiot still believes
that rabbits live on the moon.

63
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,916
Pearls are tears of mermaids?

64
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:21,751
Then what are black pearls?

65
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,878
Were the mermaids wearing mascara?

66
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,673
God! That naive fool.

67
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,594
How is she going to survive
in this tough world?

68
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:34,680
Damn it!

69
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:41,604
POSTS

70
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:42,772
I'm sorry.

71
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:45,525
When you're having jajangmyeon in heaven,

72
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:49,028
ask them to put an egg on top.

73
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:51,489
When we meet again,

74
00:08:52,448 --> 00:08:53,824
I'll buy you a proper jajangmyeon.

75
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:19,178
KIM HUI-JU

76
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,398
Did your guardian go somewhere?

77
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:35,319
Oh, my husband? He went to work.

78
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:39,698
I asked Director Kwon,
and he said you can eat gimbap.

79
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:42,243
Thank you.

80
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:45,329
I love gimbap.

81
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:49,417
This is called cherry blossom gimbap.

82
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:52,920
If you didn't get to see
the cherry blossoms in the spring,

83
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:55,089
you can have this gimbap instead.

84
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,177
I didn't know such gimbap existed.

85
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,514
What does it look like?

86
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:09,061
I can't really see because of my illness.

87
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:19,947
It's so good.

88
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:23,075
I think I know what it looks like
now that I've tasted it.

89
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:32,710
This

90
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,546
is plum blossom tea.

91
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:40,176
Have this tea while you eat gimbap
so that you don't choke on it.

92
00:12:46,056 --> 00:12:48,601
The tea smells like plum blossoms.

93
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:52,021
I could smell cherry blossoms
from the gimbap.

94
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:59,445
Please tell me
if you ever have cravings for anything.

95
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:02,406
I'll make whatever I can.

96
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:06,744
Dr. Lee Jun made
a beautiful plate for you.

97
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:10,831
Jun did?

98
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,209
Yes. He asked me

99
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:15,711
to make sure you get it,

100
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:19,006
but I told him I'd give it to you
with food on it.

101
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:23,469
Gosh, that fool.

102
00:13:24,803 --> 00:13:28,807
I thought he had smashed everything,
but I guess he had saved one.

103
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:51,914
Thank you, chef.

104
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:07,638
Can I ask you one more question?

105
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:10,516
Why did Dr. Lee Kang

106
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:14,478
come to the hospice?

107
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:18,107
Because he's a surgeon
who no longer can perform surgery.

108
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,443
Why not? Why can't he operate on patients?

109
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:23,946
Ask him directly if you're curious.

110
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:19,251
HAPPY BIRTHDAY

111
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:31,639
Hello. I'm Ye-sol, Min-yong's friend.

112
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:35,643
Ji-yong hasn't had a chance to learn
the alphabet because of his illness,

113
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:38,896
so I'm writing down what he's saying.

114
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:54,703
We're here.

115
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:25,192
Right, I forgot.

116
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,027
Thank you.

117
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:29,655
Dr. Lee, are you coming with me?

118
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:32,992
Yes.

119
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:37,079
NEUROSURGERY SEO HYEON-CHEOL

120
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,038
Just a second.

121
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,751
-Hey, what's up?
-We have a problem, Kang.

122
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:45,421
Remember the AVM patient, Park Pil-ho?

123
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:47,548
He was brought to the ER
because of a seizure

124
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:49,049
caused by alcohol consumption.

125
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,093
We wanted to know
if he needed another embolization

126
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:52,344
-or radiation...
-I'm going in!

127
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:54,138
-Wait!
-You were his doctor, you know.

128
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,390
That patient already finished
his first AVM embolization.

129
00:16:56,473 --> 00:16:59,309
He needs radiosurgery,
but he never came back.

130
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,522
Can you explain
his current condition again?

131
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,068
Ms. Moon.

132
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:11,488
You can make your payment
and pick up your prescription.

133
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:13,115
Okay, thank you.

134
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,869
I thought I might not see you this year.

135
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,288
It's not getting worse or anything,

136
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:23,083
but I came to get
my medication just in case.

137
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:24,585
Oh, right.

138
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:27,671
I heard you work
at the cafeteria in our hospice.

139
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:29,256
Yes.

140
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:32,051
I heard
Dr. Lee Kang transferred there too.

141
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:34,636
I met him.

142
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:37,973
Hello.

143
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,102
Did you see where the little boy
who just came here went?

144
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:44,688
A boy? I didn't see him.
Who are you talking about?

145
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,482
-Can we pay?
-Sorry about that.

146
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:49,318
-What's our total?
-It's 90,000 won.

147
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:50,903
-Did you enjoy the food?
-Yes, we did.

148
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:08,420
I'm sorry.

149
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:14,635
Ji-yong.

150
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:23,185
Ji-yong!

151
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,023
Yun Ji-yong!

152
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:37,574
What are you talking about?

153
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:39,868
What do you mean, you lost Ji-yong?

154
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:42,121
Where are you?

155
00:18:43,038 --> 00:18:44,039
Where?

156
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:45,833
Gongju?

157
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:48,585
Yes, I just called the police now.

158
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:50,754
I'll keep looking.

159
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,173
I'm sorry.

160
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:08,063
Why did Dr. Lee Kang
transfer to the hospice?

161
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:11,233
There's something wrong with his wrist.

162
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:13,443
Neurosurgeons often perform surgery

163
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,113
for small blood vessels in the brain,

164
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:18,323
so their hands are very important.

165
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,659
But his hand started shaking
during surgery,

166
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:23,495
so he was taken out
before he could even finish it.

167
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,234
Min-yong.

168
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,153
Cha-young.

169
00:19:57,154 --> 00:19:59,114
What's wrong? Did something happen?

170
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:05,746
Ji-yong...

171
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:09,124
Did something

172
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,501
happen to Ji-yong?

173
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:20,928
That crazy idiot.
I'll kill him when I find him!

174
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:26,975
I have to go find him. Can you lend me
some money for the bus fare?

175
00:20:37,527 --> 00:20:40,489
SEOUL, GONGJU

176
00:20:47,162 --> 00:20:50,082
It's okay. We'll find him.

177
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,167
There, there.

178
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,379
You're looking for a kid?

179
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:58,632
Yes. I saw him going inside earlier
but can't find him.

180
00:20:58,715 --> 00:21:01,260
It's a seven-year-old boy.
He's about this tall.

181
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:03,971
The one wearing a big T-shirt.

182
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:07,266
His eyes looked like those
of a startled frog. Is that him?

183
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:08,684
Yes, it is. Did you see him?

184
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,645
I wonder if he's that Seoul lady's son.

185
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:13,063
"Seoul lady"?

186
00:21:13,146 --> 00:21:15,357
There's a young woman
who's originally from Seoul,

187
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:19,236
but she vanished
in the middle of washing the dishes.

188
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:21,196
She has eyes

189
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,907
that look like a startled frog's, too.

190
00:21:24,491 --> 00:21:27,077
Then could I get
her contact information or address?

191
00:21:28,078 --> 00:21:30,580
I don't have her contact information.

192
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:33,667
But I heard she lives at a building

193
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,919
near Gongju Church,
or somewhere like that.

194
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,186
-Hey, kid!
-Dr. Lee.

195
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:59,609
I have my mom's address.
Ji-yong must be there.

196
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:01,278
What's the address?

197
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:03,530
Here.

198
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:09,411
But I promised her

199
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,457
that I'd never visit her again.

200
00:22:21,798 --> 00:22:23,342
Isn't that Ji-yong?

201
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:26,386
Ji-yong!

202
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:28,597
Yun Ji-yong.

203
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:33,310
You crazy idiot.
What the heck are you doing here?

204
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:34,394
Min-yong.

205
00:22:37,105 --> 00:22:38,356
Cha-young.

206
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:40,400
Dr. Lee.

207
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:43,487
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

208
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:46,198
Min-yong, don't cry.

209
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:48,492
I'm fine.

210
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:51,536
Yes. We found Ji-yong, so it's all good.

211
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:53,580
Don't worry.

212
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,251
Did you see your mom?

213
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:01,630
Yes.

214
00:23:02,089 --> 00:23:06,468
She gave me money,
saying I should get something nice to eat.

215
00:23:08,261 --> 00:23:09,513
Where is she now?

216
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:12,099
She told me to get something nice to eat

217
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:14,267
and never visit her again.

218
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:17,270
Cha-young is asking you where Mom is now.

219
00:23:20,315 --> 00:23:23,068
What is it? Did something happen to her?

220
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:28,281
The man mom lives with,

221
00:23:28,865 --> 00:23:31,159
he beat her up.

222
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:47,592
Ji-yong is okay, but his brother
Min-yong suddenly collapsed.

223
00:23:47,676 --> 00:23:48,885
We're at the hospital now.

224
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:52,931
His BT is 38.2 degrees.
He has nausea and is vomiting,

225
00:23:53,014 --> 00:23:54,641
so he's on an IV at the moment.

226
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:56,935
Yes, I'll bring them back tonight.

227
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,521
Okay.

228
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:04,526
Did you fall ill because I worried you?

229
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:08,989
Yes, so don't disappear on me
without a word again.

230
00:24:10,699 --> 00:24:14,119
Okay. From now on, I'll make sure
I tell you before I disappear.

231
00:24:14,828 --> 00:24:17,414
Just don't disappear on me ever again.

232
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:21,168
Stay glued to me at all times, okay?

233
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:23,003
Okay.

234
00:24:23,753 --> 00:24:24,796
Promise.

235
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,383
Stamp. Promise sealed.

236
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:38,310
-Are you all right?
-Yes, I feel totally fine now.

237
00:24:57,621 --> 00:24:59,122
I don't feel sick at all.

238
00:24:59,706 --> 00:25:00,707
I know.

239
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:03,835
-Then you won't scold me, right?
-We'll see about that.

240
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:05,378
Min-yong.

241
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:09,299
Please forgive my brother, Dr. Lee.

242
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,386
Where is Cha-young?

243
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:18,808
Ji-yong forgot to give Mom a gift.

244
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:21,895
So Cha-young said she'd bring it to Mom.

245
00:25:45,001 --> 00:25:47,879
Mom. It's me, Cha-young.

246
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:50,840
I'm waiting for you at the department
store. Why aren't you coming?

247
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:54,386
I've been here for three hours already.
When are you coming?

248
00:25:56,304 --> 00:25:57,889
I'll wait on the first floor.

249
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:01,601
Mom...

250
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:21,621
Excuse me.

251
00:26:22,747 --> 00:26:24,541
Is this Jangmi Townhouse?

252
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:29,087
I'm sorry,

253
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:32,549
but do you know Ms. Yang Seung-hui

254
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:35,427
who lives

255
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:40,140
in Jangmi Townhouse?

256
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,567
I'm sorry,

257
00:26:52,068 --> 00:26:54,738
but do you know Min-yong and Ji-yong?

258
00:27:04,914 --> 00:27:08,918
This is a birthday gift
from Ji-yong for his mom.

259
00:27:09,711 --> 00:27:11,671
If you know Ji-yong's mom,

260
00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:15,967
will you please give this to her?

261
