00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:47,416
Does he even report to you
every time I go to the bathroom?

526
00:43:47,499 --> 00:43:50,252
Why are they blaming the doctor
for Chairman Jo's death?

527
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:53,088
Do they think doctors are idiots?

528
00:43:54,590 --> 00:43:55,758
Let's keep this between us.

529
00:43:55,841 --> 00:43:58,427
But Chairman Jo would've passed away
a long time ago

530
00:43:58,510 --> 00:44:00,638
if it weren't for the doctors
at this hospital.

531
00:44:04,516 --> 00:44:05,601
Oh, I see.

532
00:44:06,685 --> 00:44:08,187
Did you change your strategy?

533
00:44:09,063 --> 00:44:11,899
I'd love to show you a few tears
and act like I'm touched.

534
00:44:13,359 --> 00:44:15,277
But I'm too exhausted for that.

535
00:44:15,361 --> 00:44:17,780
I read about Chairman Jo's death
on the internet.

536
00:44:17,863 --> 00:44:20,324
And I heard his reckless son
punched the doctor-in-charge

537
00:44:20,407 --> 00:44:22,284
because everyone kept talking about it.

538
00:44:22,368 --> 00:44:25,537
I'm just here for something personal.

539
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:28,165
-I came to meet--
-Dr. Lee Kang.

540
00:44:30,542 --> 00:44:33,045
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting.

541
00:44:33,253 --> 00:44:35,047
Thank you for seeing me.
I know you're busy.

542
00:44:35,130 --> 00:44:36,131
No, it's okay.

543
00:44:36,715 --> 00:44:39,385
-Have you been well?
-Yes, I'm doing well.

544
00:44:39,551 --> 00:44:40,719
I'm here to ask you something.

545
00:44:40,803 --> 00:44:41,804
Okay.

546
00:44:43,138 --> 00:44:45,808
Okay, just a second.

547
00:44:45,891 --> 00:44:47,434
There we go.

548
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:54,650
Give me your hand.

549
00:44:58,695 --> 00:44:59,905
Guess what this is.

550
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:03,867
It's a flower ring.

551
00:45:05,202 --> 00:45:06,203
Doesn't it smell nice?

552
00:45:07,496 --> 00:45:09,039
Isn't he

553
00:45:09,832 --> 00:45:11,834
such a romantic husband?

554
00:45:13,043 --> 00:45:17,256
I'd love to have a husband like him
for at least one day.

555
00:45:18,298 --> 00:45:21,093
Or at least for half a day
if an entire day is too long.

556
00:45:21,343 --> 00:45:22,428
Me too.

557
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:24,304
Me too.

558
00:45:25,139 --> 00:45:27,141
You already had your share of romance.

559
00:45:27,266 --> 00:45:30,686
That darn old man was really nice to you

560
00:45:30,769 --> 00:45:32,104
because you gave birth to a son.

561
00:45:32,187 --> 00:45:33,939
I get a headache

562
00:45:34,022 --> 00:45:36,191
every time I think about that.

563
00:45:39,069 --> 00:45:40,028
What?

564
00:45:40,529 --> 00:45:43,449
You always give me candy
every time you're out of words.

565
00:45:47,244 --> 00:45:50,706
Peppermint candy tastes the best.

566
00:45:52,708 --> 00:45:53,834
That's enough.

567
00:45:54,126 --> 00:45:57,296
Too much candy will make my teeth rot.

568
00:46:00,799 --> 00:46:02,176
Hey.

569
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:05,762
Don't you also want
an amazing husband like him?

570
00:46:07,347 --> 00:46:10,267
I once had an amazing husband as well.

571
00:46:10,684 --> 00:46:14,271
But I ended up leaving him
because I was out of my mind.

572
00:46:14,354 --> 00:46:17,816
Exactly. You should've known
that he was a catch.

573
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:19,193
You were such a fool.

574
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:25,032
You should never let go
of that amazing guy like I did.

575
00:46:25,115 --> 00:46:26,116
Okay.

576
00:46:27,367 --> 00:46:28,368
What?

577
00:46:30,162 --> 00:46:31,497
I should go check on the gomtang.

578
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:34,291
What? What do you mean?

579
00:46:39,671 --> 00:46:40,881
What did she mean by that?

580
00:46:41,423 --> 00:46:42,841
"That amazing guy"?

581
00:46:44,384 --> 00:46:46,345
It sounded like

582
00:46:46,595 --> 00:46:49,306
she was referring to someone.

583
00:46:49,848 --> 00:46:50,933
Yes, it did.

584
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:52,518
Right?

585
00:46:53,101 --> 00:46:56,021
Did it also sound
a little peculiar to you?

586
00:46:56,939 --> 00:46:57,773
Yes.

587
00:46:58,899 --> 00:47:01,276
Then who do you think is the amazing guy

588
00:47:02,694 --> 00:47:03,904
she was talking about?

589
00:47:32,140 --> 00:47:34,601
Ms. Han, can you give me some kimchi?

590
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:36,353
Why do you want kimchi?

591
00:47:36,436 --> 00:47:37,854
I saw Director Kwon eat cup noodles,

592
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:39,523
and now I want one for myself.

593
00:47:39,606 --> 00:47:41,441
But I can't have noodles without kimchi.

594
00:47:44,278 --> 00:47:46,863
Where is Director Kwon?

595
00:48:16,101 --> 00:48:17,352
My goodness!

596
00:48:22,566 --> 00:48:23,609
What are you doing here?

597
00:48:24,776 --> 00:48:26,987
Who said you could come in my office?

598
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:30,407
Well, the thing is...

599
00:48:32,242 --> 00:48:36,163
I heard you ate cup noodles a while ago.

600
00:48:37,247 --> 00:48:40,709
The beef bone broth we recently got
tastes really delicious.

601
00:48:40,792 --> 00:48:43,837
So I thought you should try some
while it's still warm.

602
00:48:51,887 --> 00:48:53,639
I don't want it. You can take it back.

603
00:48:54,931 --> 00:48:57,184
You always seem to be
eating instant noodles.

604
00:48:57,851 --> 00:48:59,353
You should eat some proper food.

605
00:48:59,436 --> 00:49:01,313
I like instant noodles

606
00:49:01,396 --> 00:49:04,566
way better than the food you make.

607
00:49:05,275 --> 00:49:06,568
So just take it back.

608
00:49:07,903 --> 00:49:09,696
I already added glass noodles.

609
00:49:10,155 --> 00:49:12,783
You're the only one who can eat it now.

610
00:49:12,866 --> 00:49:16,203
And I know you hate throwing away food.

611
00:49:16,328 --> 00:49:18,163
Will you please eat it just this once?

612
00:49:18,246 --> 00:49:19,956
I told you I don't want it!

613
00:49:20,040 --> 00:49:23,710
Either give it to an animal
or throw it away in the trash!

614
00:49:25,879 --> 00:49:27,714
Just do whatever you want.

615
00:50:15,512 --> 00:50:17,681
This is so delicious.

616
00:50:18,306 --> 00:50:20,016
Slow down. You'll get an upset stomach.

617
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:25,230
Will you slow down? I won't steal any!

618
00:50:28,233 --> 00:50:29,651
My gosh, that was nice.

619
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:34,114
Why do you eat so quickly?

620
00:50:34,197 --> 00:50:35,365
Is someone chasing you?

621
00:50:35,449 --> 00:50:37,909
Yes, there were always people chasing us.

622
00:50:38,285 --> 00:50:39,411
So I had to eat quickly.

623
00:50:39,494 --> 00:50:40,996
That kind of become a habit of mine.

624
00:50:42,122 --> 00:50:43,540
What are you talking about?

625
00:50:45,125 --> 00:50:47,919
My mom always ran away
after she borrowed money.

626
00:50:48,003 --> 00:50:50,213
She abandoned my sister and kept me.

627
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:53,091
I'm serious.

628
00:50:53,592 --> 00:50:56,261
And I don't know how creditors do it,

629
00:50:56,344 --> 00:50:57,637
but they'd always chase us down.

630
00:50:57,721 --> 00:50:59,514
We always had to be ready to run.

631
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:02,225
Don't be like that.

632
00:51:02,476 --> 00:51:06,104
From now on, you should
get used to eating your food more slowly.

633
00:51:06,188 --> 00:51:07,647
Make a new habit.

634
00:51:07,731 --> 00:51:10,108
Otherwise, you'll become
really sick one day.

635
00:51:11,318 --> 00:51:12,402
Okay.

636
00:51:13,528 --> 00:51:14,362
My goodness.

637
00:51:16,573 --> 00:51:18,533
Do you have more gomtang?

638
00:51:18,784 --> 00:51:19,951
I haven't had this in a while.

639
00:51:20,035 --> 00:51:22,746
My gosh, it's so delicious.

640
00:51:22,829 --> 00:51:23,955
I haven't had gomtang

641
00:51:24,039 --> 00:51:26,833
ever since that incident in Greece.

642
00:51:26,917 --> 00:51:29,044
What do those things
have to do with each other?

643
00:51:29,127 --> 00:51:30,670
It's a long story.

644
00:51:30,754 --> 00:51:34,382
You know Dr. Lee Kang, the new doctor?

645
00:51:34,466 --> 00:51:36,968
My gosh, that punk...

646
00:51:37,636 --> 00:51:38,637
"Lee Kang."

647
00:51:39,513 --> 00:51:41,848
Why does that name sound familiar?
It's not even that common.

648
00:51:42,808 --> 00:51:43,934
"Lee Kang."

649
00:51:44,810 --> 00:51:45,894
"Lee Kang"?

650
00:51:47,479 --> 00:51:50,065
Why does it sound so familiar?

651
00:51:50,148 --> 00:51:52,150
What is this?
Am I confusing him with Lee Kang-in?

652
00:51:52,234 --> 00:51:53,693
I'll get you more gomtang.

653
00:51:53,777 --> 00:51:55,862
This time, make sure
you chew on your food.

654
00:51:55,946 --> 00:51:58,240
-I want you to eat for 30 minutes.
-Eureka!

655
00:52:00,283 --> 00:52:02,619
I finally remember that name.

656
00:52:03,453 --> 00:52:06,998
The name of Cha-young's first love.
It's Lee Kang!

657
00:52:17,926 --> 00:52:19,344
-Thank you.
-No problem.

658
00:52:23,306 --> 00:52:25,809
-The number of people who suffered damage
-Potatoes...

659
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:28,311
adds up to about 200 people.

660
00:52:28,395 --> 00:52:31,690
And the cost of damage is
estimated to be over six billion won.

661
00:52:32,274 --> 00:52:33,358
Here's our next news.

662
00:52:33,441 --> 00:52:36,570
A four-story shopping mall
in Gwangjin-gu, Seoul

663
00:52:36,653 --> 00:52:39,406
collapsed today at around 12:20 p.m.

664
00:52:39,781 --> 00:52:40,740
Due to the collapse,

665
00:52:40,824 --> 00:52:43,869
two laborers from the first floor
got buried underneath

666
00:52:43,952 --> 00:52:46,705
including a woman in her sixties
and a seven-year-old kid

667
00:52:46,788 --> 00:52:48,957
who were apparently on the fourth floor,

668
00:52:49,040 --> 00:52:51,126
and they are currently
in the process of being rescued.

669
00:52:51,793 --> 00:52:54,170
The fire department announced

670
00:52:54,254 --> 00:52:56,089
that they are currently

671
00:52:56,172 --> 00:52:59,759
searching for additional casualties
from the second and third floor.

672
00:53:02,387 --> 00:53:04,055
You know Ms. Moon Cha-young, right?

673
00:53:04,639 --> 00:53:06,057
She's a chef.

674
00:53:06,141 --> 00:53:08,351
And I noticed that she's been
receiving treatment

675
00:53:08,435 --> 00:53:10,520
from a psychiatrist at our hospital
ever since 2006.

676
00:53:11,479 --> 00:53:14,024
What happened to Ms. Moon?

677
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:21,364
Mom.

678
00:53:23,366 --> 00:53:24,451
Mom.

679
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:42,844
Are you okay?

680
00:53:43,887 --> 00:53:45,555
Are you carsick?

681
00:53:47,599 --> 00:53:50,185
Should I stop the car?

682
00:53:50,810 --> 00:53:52,520
My goodness.

683
00:54:00,278 --> 00:54:02,781
What happened to Ms. Moon?

684
00:54:03,281 --> 00:54:04,783
Ms. Moon...

685
00:54:04,866 --> 00:54:07,953
She was buried underneath
the collapsed department store that day.

686
00:54:09,162 --> 00:54:11,414
She was only 12 years old.

687
00:54:13,041 --> 00:54:16,753
My mom was also
at the department store that day.

688
00:54:17,712 --> 00:54:20,507
She was only 12 years old.

689
00:54:21,174 --> 00:54:22,968
She must've been so scared.

690
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:56,876
-Thank you.
-No problem.

691
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:59,504
You almost forgot her bag.

692
00:54:59,754 --> 00:55:01,756
-Oh, right.
-Here.

693
00:55:02,048 --> 00:55:03,675
-Thank you.
-No problem.

694
00:55:06,678 --> 00:55:08,179
My goodness.

695
00:55:09,472 --> 00:55:13,059
Did you happen to see Cha-young
on your way here?

696
00:55:13,643 --> 00:55:14,728
No.

697
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:17,564
She was on her way back
from getting groceries,

698
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:19,107
but she got carsick and got off.

699
00:55:19,190 --> 00:55:21,192
She just sent the cab driver here
on his own.

700
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:24,112
My goodness.

701
00:55:24,195 --> 00:55:26,281
She left her wallet and cell phone
in her bag.

702
00:55:26,489 --> 00:55:28,533
My goodness.

703
00:55:28,616 --> 00:55:29,868
Dr. Lee!

704
00:55:29,951 --> 00:55:31,870
You didn't answer any of our calls again.

705
00:55:31,953 --> 00:55:33,830
Grandma Suk-ja suddenly collapsed.

706
00:55:33,913 --> 00:55:35,874
Her systolic blood pressure is 70.

707
00:55:42,255 --> 00:55:43,631
Hello.

708
00:55:51,306 --> 00:55:53,058
She has temporary low blood pressure.

709
00:55:53,141 --> 00:55:54,392
Her pulse rate is slowing down.

710
00:55:54,517 --> 00:55:56,186
She'll go into shock if she's dehydrated.

711
00:55:56,269 --> 00:55:58,396
So give her 500ml of normal saline.

712
00:55:58,480 --> 00:56:00,607
-Keep her legs above heart level.
-Okay.

713
00:56:03,818 --> 00:56:05,403
My goodness, ma'am!

714
00:56:05,487 --> 00:56:06,696
-Ma'am!
-Ma'am!

715
00:56:06,780 --> 00:56:07,655
Ma'am!

716
00:56:34,182 --> 00:56:36,184
Grandma Suk-ja, you shouldn't be here.

717
00:56:36,267 --> 00:56:38,603
You need to go back
and get your injection--

718
00:56:38,686 --> 00:56:40,522
What's wrong with her?

719
00:56:40,605 --> 00:56:42,816
I'm the one who's terminally ill.

720
00:56:42,899 --> 00:56:44,734
What's the matter with her?

721
00:56:46,152 --> 00:56:50,031
Ms. Jang, she went into temporary shock
because she was startled by you.

722
00:56:50,115 --> 00:56:53,159
-We need to take care of you right now.
-I'm okay.

723
00:56:53,243 --> 00:56:55,245
See? As you can see,

724
00:56:55,328 --> 00:56:56,955
I'm perfectly conscious

725
00:56:57,038 --> 00:56:58,581
even without an injection.

726
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:00,375
Ms. Jang.

727
00:57:00,458 --> 00:57:02,836
Why would you get shocked because of me?

728
00:57:02,919 --> 00:57:05,839
It's not like you're my daughter

729
00:57:05,922 --> 00:57:07,298
or my little sister.

730
00:57:07,382 --> 00:57:10,093
You and I aren't even related by blood.

731
00:57:10,718 --> 00:57:13,471
Why would you get shocked because of me?

732
00:57:13,555 --> 00:57:15,390
Please wake up. Come to your senses.

733
00:57:15,473 --> 00:57:17,517
Ma'am, you need to go back to your room.

734
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:18,685
-Let me take you.
-Come on.

735
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:20,687
Will you please wake up?

736
00:57:20,770 --> 00:57:22,939
Please stop. You need to calm down.

737
00:57:58,933 --> 00:58:00,185
Hello, is this the cafeteria?

738
00:58:00,768 --> 00:58:03,146
I'm sorry, but I called to ask
if Ms. Moon came back.

739
00:58:32,926 --> 00:58:35,470
Hey, it's you. Hello.

740
00:58:35,553 --> 00:58:37,055
I thought it might be you.

741
00:58:37,388 --> 00:58:38,848
What are you doing here?

742
00:58:39,057 --> 00:58:40,475
Oh, well...

743
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:44,103
I got car sick while I was in a cab,
so I got out.

744
00:58:44,187 --> 00:58:46,481
And now, I'm on my way back
to the hospital.

745
00:59:16,594 --> 00:59:18,805
Are these for Ms. Kim Hui-ju?

746
00:59:22,183 --> 00:59:24,185
Well, not exactly.

747
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:27,897
I just had a crappy day.

748
00:59:30,733 --> 00:59:33,903
And on my way home,
I happened to see a bungeo-ppang cart.

749
00:59:34,779 --> 00:59:36,322
So I bought some.

750
00:59:38,408 --> 00:59:39,993
But then I realized

751
00:59:40,994 --> 00:59:42,620
that I don't like bungeo-ppang.

752
00:59:43,371 --> 00:59:46,874
Then I suddenly remembered
that Hui-ju used to like them.

753
00:59:50,628 --> 00:59:53,506
And before I knew it, I was already
headed this way like a lunatic.

754
01:00:14,944 --> 01:00:16,404
I'll make sure

755
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:20,325
to give these to Ms. Kim Hui-ju.

756
01:00:20,908 --> 01:00:24,037
I'll plate them on the pretty plate
you made for her.

757
01:00:40,261 --> 01:00:42,055
What happened

758
01:00:43,389 --> 01:00:45,850
to Dr. Lee Kang's wrist?

759
01:00:47,435 --> 01:00:49,604
I heard he came out
in the middle of a surgery

760
01:00:49,812 --> 01:00:52,732
because something was wrong
with his wrist.

761
01:00:54,776 --> 01:00:58,655
And apparently,
that's why he ended up here.

762
01:01:04,619 --> 01:01:05,745
By any chance,

763
01:01:07,955 --> 01:01:09,624
does Kang like you?

764
01:02:04,512 --> 01:02:06,764
Hello, this is Geosung Hospice.

765
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:08,474
Hello, I'm Lee Kang.

766
01:02:08,558 --> 01:02:10,768
Did Ms. Moon happen to come back...

767
01:02:12,770 --> 01:02:15,231
Never mind.
I called by mistake. I'm sorry.

768
01:02:48,222 --> 01:02:49,056
There.

769
01:02:58,357 --> 01:03:01,152
Min-seong always helped me
prepare your memorial service.

770
01:03:02,195 --> 01:03:03,905
But he's not here anymore.

771
01:03:04,530 --> 01:03:05,698
So

772
01:03:07,033 --> 01:03:08,534
let's just drink by ourselves.

773
01:03:09,577 --> 01:03:11,996
I brought you shrimp crackers,
your favorite snack.

774
01:03:15,041 --> 01:03:16,584
I came outside

775
01:03:16,667 --> 01:03:18,711
so we could get some fresh air.
That's okay, right?

776
01:03:34,018 --> 01:03:35,478
Here you are.

777
01:03:41,442 --> 01:03:43,903
Ms. Han told me

778
01:03:44,737 --> 01:03:45,947
that you looked for me.

779
01:03:49,534 --> 01:03:52,662
I wanted to ask
if you'd like to drink with me after work.

780
01:04:03,923 --> 01:04:06,425
That's my mom's seat.

781
01:04:06,801 --> 01:04:07,969
You can sit here.

782
01:04:35,288 --> 01:04:36,747
Isn't that water?

783
01:04:37,331 --> 01:04:40,001
You should drink water
since you're not feeling so well.

784
01:04:54,181 --> 01:04:55,516
Happy birthday.

785
01:05:08,487 --> 01:05:10,364
I hope you're never sick again.

786
01:05:10,948 --> 01:05:12,158
Especially on your birthdays.

787
01:06:06,170 --> 01:06:09,340
I'm sure he's better than you.
You're not even doing anything.

